A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Expanding Home Ownership Opportunities for
2 Georgians; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia General Assembly affirmed by law that "housing is an issue of
4 paramount concern to this state which affects the health, welfare, and safety of the citizens
5 of this state and the economic viability and planned growth of its communities"; and
6 WHEREAS, Georgia is currently ranked as the most at risk state in the nation for housing
7 market disruptions, rental increases, and unsafe conditions from private equity investment
8 in housing; and
9 WHEREAS, three corporate landlords own over 19,000 homes in the metro Atlanta area,
10 constituting nearly 11 percent of the single family homes available for rent in Fulton,
11 Clayton, DeKalb, Gwinnett, and Cobb Counties; and
12 WHEREAS, out-of-state institutional investors own 30 percent of all single family rental
13 stock in Atlanta; and
